        "timestamp": "2021-03-10 13:11:17.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> Patch Set 1: Code-Review+1\n> \n> The way this is muddying up DefaultPfDao, I'm beginning to wonder if we should go back and make PfReferenceTimestampKey Embeddable again.  That may entail lifting duplicate code from the current superclass, which would probably trigger a complaint from sonar, but isolating that to one class, PfReferenceTimestampKey, seems preferable to me.\n\nYeah. Not seeing any alternative way than making PfReferenceKey as Embedded, to avoid duplication of code. I believe there wont be further changes needed on DefaultPfDao apart from this one. Incase this brings in further more changes in DefaultPfDao then we will decide if we can make this PfReferenceTimestampKey class a isolated one, including the properties of PfReferenceKey. Thanks Jim.",
